The paper focuses on computing n-gram statistics for information retrieval and natural language processing, which are key areas in computer science. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses algorithms and methods for distributed data processing, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper includes experiments and analysis of the methods, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
